President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the state of Maryland, providing federal aid to assist with recovery efforts after severe storms and flooding occurred in July 2016. The declaration allows for federal funding to be used for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Timothy Manner has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the area, and additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA news desk.